# Distributed Tracing

<%= baseName %> includes built-in distributed tracing support using OpenTelemetry for microservices and gateway applications.

> **Note:** Distributed tracing is only available for microservice and gateway application types. Monolith applications do not include this feature.

## Overview

<%_ if (distributedTracingZipkin) { _%>
The application exports trace spans to **Zipkin** via the Zipkin HTTP API. All requests are automatically instrumented through the `tracing` and `tracing-opentelemetry` integration.
<%_ } else if (distributedTracingJaeger) { _%>
The application exports trace spans to **Jaeger** via the OpenTelemetry Protocol (OTLP) over gRPC. All requests are automatically instrumented through the `tracing` and `tracing-opentelemetry` integration.
<%_ } _%>

Distributed tracing allows you to:

- Track requests as they flow across multiple services
- Identify latency bottlenecks in your microservices architecture
- Visualize service dependencies and call graphs
- Debug issues by examining individual trace spans

## Configuration

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Description | Default |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `TRACING_ENABLED` | Enable/disable distributed tracing | `true` |
| `TRACING_SERVICE_NAME` | Service name reported in traces | `<%= baseName %>` |
<%_ if (distributedTracingZipkin) { _%>
| `TRACING_ENDPOINT` | Zipkin collector endpoint | `http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans` |
<%_ } else if (distributedTracingJaeger) { _%>
| `TRACING_ENDPOINT` | Jaeger OTLP gRPC endpoint | `http://localhost:4317` |
<%_ } _%>
| `TRACING_SAMPLE_RATIO` | Sampling ratio (0.0 to 1.0) | `1.0` |

### Example Configuration

```bash
# Enable tracing (default)
TRACING_ENABLED=true
TRACING_SERVICE_NAME=<%= baseName %>

<%_ if (distributedTracingZipkin) { _%>
# Zipkin endpoint
TRACING_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans
<%_ } else if (distributedTracingJaeger) { _%>
# Jaeger OTLP endpoint
TRACING_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:4317
<%_ } _%>

# Sample 50% of traces in production
TRACING_SAMPLE_RATIO=0.5

# Disable tracing
TRACING_ENABLED=false
```

## Running the Tracing Backend

### Using Docker Compose

The project includes a Docker Compose file for the tracing backend:

```bash
# Start the tracing backend
docker compose -f docker/tracing.yml up -d

# View logs
docker compose -f docker/tracing.yml logs -f

# Stop the tracing backend
docker compose -f docker/tracing.yml down
```

